A City Harvest Fair

On Saturday, Aug. 18, the annual City Gardeners' Harvest Fair will be held at the Gateway National Recreation Area at Floyd Bennett Field in Brooklyn.

The fair, from 11 A.M. to 6 P.M., will have food to sample, country music, square-dancing, hayrides, games and demonstrations of milking cows and making honey. Admission is free.

City gardeners in the five boroughs can compete for blue ribbons in 28 categories, mostly for home-grown vegetables.

Entries must be brought to the Cornell Pavilion Registration Booth at the park on Friday, Aug. 17, between 4 and 7 P.M., or on Saturday, from 10 A.M. to noon. Complete contest rules are available from Operation Green Thumb, (212) 233-2926.